sentences.english: First, each partition has its own subset of metadata.

sentences.english: The first is to simply use completely separate subsets.
sentences.chinese: 第一種僅僅是使用完全獨立的子集。

sentences.english: Subdivision of the tetrahedrons using minimal element subdivision.
sentences.chinese: 採用最小子集法實現四面體單元分裂。

sentences.english: A graph-based ant system was proposed for solving subset problems.
sentences.chinese: 提出了一種求解子集問題的基於圖的螞蟻系統。

sentences.english: Service programs are a subset of console applications.

sentences.english: These subsets differ from user to user and from need to need.

sentences.english: Therefore, the user-specific model is a subset of the portal pages.

sentences.chinese: 通過數據抽樣，只需掃描數據的一個子集即可。

sentences.english: This article showed code examples for a small, but common, subset of commands.
sentences.chinese: 本文提供了一小部分常用命令子集的代碼示例。

sentences.english: Each installation type installs a different subset of packages.
sentences.chinese: 每種安裝類型安裝不同的軟件包子集。

sentences.english: Then you will receive an error message when selecting this subset.
sentences.chinese: 然後在選擇這個子集時您會收到一條錯誤消息。

sentences.english: This allows applications to link only the subset of libraries it needs.
sentences.chinese: 這允許應用程序按需鏈接庫的子集。
